  "eventMetadata": {
    "context_description": "Trader consensus reflects near-certainty of no US-Iran nuclear deal by April 30, driven by the collapse of indirect negotiations in Islamabad last week, where talks ended without agreement on core issues like Iran's uranium enrichment suspension and US sanctions relief. A fragile two-week ceasefire, brokered by Pakistan on April 8 and partially extended, faces strain from the ongoing US naval blockade of the Strait of Hormuz, which Iran cites as a precondition for resuming diplomacy. Recent US envoy dispatches, including Witkoff and Kushner to Pakistan on April 24, yielded no breakthrough amid mutual recriminations and hardened positions. With just days remaining, entrenched distrust from prior JCPOA withdrawal and escalation risks outweigh slim prospects for sudden concessions, though an 11th-hour mediated pact could theoretically shift odds.",
    "context_requires_regen": false,
    "context_updated_at": "2026-04-27T07:02:37.166Z"
  }
